2026-01-11 11:05:39.078145+00	2026-01-11 11:05:39.095948+00	b144e17e-1945-4aa0-b0da-c402162a595e	2026-01-12 13:38:34.115334+00	cenote-diving-yucatan	Cenote Diving in the Yucatan: An Underground Adventure	published	public	[]	[]	Cenote Diving in the Yucatan: An Underground Adventure	Explore the mystical underwater caves of Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula, where crystal-clear freshwater, ancient formations, and Mayan history converge.			index, follow	{"meta": {"path": "/cenote-diving-yucatan/", "slug": "cenote-diving-yucatan", "title": "Cenote Diving in the Yucatan: An Underground Adventure", "robots": "index, follow", "seo_title": "Cenote Diving in the Yucatan: An Underground Adventure", "og_image_url": "", "seo_description": "Explore the mystical underwater caves of Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula, where crystal-clear freshwater, ancient formations, and Mayan history converge."}, "blocks": [{"id": "db478514-5144-484c-bc7f-c8031339dad0", "data": {"content": "<p>Beneath the jungle floor of Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula lies one of the world's most extensive underwater cave systems. These cenotes - natural sinkholes filled with crystal-clear freshwater - offer divers an experience unlike anything else on Earth.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 0}, {"id": "0280d0e6-2775-43a1-9085-8196bedba775", "data": {"text": "What is a Cenote?", "level": 2}, "type": "heading", "sequence": 1}, {"id": "8d117275-7cb2-4625-9634-7713c8457264", "data": {"content": "<p>Cenotes formed over millions of years as rainwater dissolved the limestone bedrock, creating vast underground river systems. When cave ceilings collapsed, they created the open pools we see today. The ancient Maya considered cenotes sacred - gateways to the underworld - and many contain archaeological artifacts.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 2}, {"id": "63bc91f8-6bdc-4306-b098-ba649c6495c7", "data": {"text": "Top Cenotes for Divers", "level": 2}, "type": "heading", "sequence": 3}, {"id": "b46a8651-fcfb-4562-a415-fb7a9eeee52f", "data": {"content": "<p><strong>Dos Ojos</strong> - Famous for its two connected caverns with spectacular light effects. Perfect for Open Water divers.</p><p><strong>The Pit</strong> - A stunning 390-foot deep sinkhole with dramatic halocline effects and ancient tree remains.</p><p><strong>Gran Cenote</strong> - Beautiful formations and excellent visibility, ideal for first-time cenote divers.</p><p><strong>Angelita</strong> - Features a ghostly \\"underwater river\\" created by a hydrogen sulfide cloud at 100 feet.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 4}, {"id": "ac2914c0-7c11-478b-aa19-15988e048086", "data": {"text": "Certification Requirements", "level": 2}, "type": "heading", "sequence": 5}, {"id": "816e3246-f55f-4898-8384-b3c44c2d9f4e", "data": {"content": "<p>Most cenote dives fall into two categories:</p><ul><li><strong>Cavern Diving</strong> - Stays within the light zone, Open Water certification required. Natural light always visible.</li><li><strong>Cave Diving</strong> - Penetrates beyond natural light. Requires specialized cave diving certification and equipment.</li></ul><p>Always dive with a certified cenote guide - these environments require specific knowledge of the systems.</p>"}, "type": "rich_text", "sequence": 6}], "version": 1, "checksum": "c71cf81596f34b9f2f10609072afca4334dd1bf9b6e484c2e5b285f6b8d8d639", "published_at": "2026-01-11T11:05:39.095780+00:00", "access_control": {"level": "public", "required_roles": [], "required_entitlements": []}, "published_by_id": "1"}	2026-01-11 11:05:39.09578+00	0	t	default	{}	1	70c922aa-9fcb-4b5e-8736-e82206cf5c37	Explore the mystical underwater caves of Mexico's Yucatan Peninsula, where crystal-clear freshwater, ancient formations, and Mayan history converge.	https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1682687220742-aba13b6e50ba?w=1200	post	7	["cenotes", "mexico", "cave diving", "cavern diving", "freshwater"]	ecf98da2-4669-4486-a712-0ac9a942fc93
